tafsir[4]{c,v,t}:
  37,2,"(And those who drive away with reproof) He also swore by the angels who drive away the clouds and bring them together."
  37,14,"(And seek to scoff when they) the people of Mecca (behold a portent) a sign such as the splitting of the moon and the eclipse of the sun."
  37,15,"(And they say: lo! This) which Muhammad (pbuh) brought us (is mere magic) a manifest lie;"
  37,17,"They asked: (And our forefathers) shall they be raised again?"